In the Matter of MORRIS WHITE PROPERTIES CORPORATION, Debtor; Weinberg & Weinberg and Leon London, Appellants, Archibald Palmer, Appellant. No. 324. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. April 10, 1939. Leon London, of New York City, pro se. Samuel Masia, of New York City, for appellant Palmer. Harold St. L. O’Dougherty, of Brooklyn, N. Y., pro se.

Before L. HAND, CLARK, and PATTERSON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Orders affirmed.
